DIPHTHERIA - BANGLADESH (03): (CHITTAGONG) FATAL, SUSPECTED, ROHINGYA REFUGEES, ex MYANMAR
******************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 19 Dec 2017 15:09 CET
Source: BFMTV [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://www.bfmtv.com/international/bangladesh-la-diphterie-fait-21-morts-dans-les-camps-rohingyas-1331206.html


The World Health Organization (WHO) said on [Tue 19 Dec 2017], 21 people died of diphtheria in Rohingya [refugee] camps in Bangladesh, where a 2nd vaccination campaign has begun, [launched on 17 Dec 2017, this time targeting minors aged 7 to 15].

According to the WHO, between [10 Nov and 17 Dec 2017], 1571 suspected cases of this disease were reported in the camps of Cox's Bazar, in [Chittagong division] southeastern Bangladesh, which host some 655 000 Rohingyas.

"About 20 percent of suspected cases" concern children under the age of 5, said a spokeswoman for WHO, Fadela Chaib, at a meeting point. press in Geneva.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[When last posted by ProMED-mail (Diphtheria - Bangladesh: fatal, susp, Rohingya refugee camp, ex Myanmar, WHO 20171214.5502309), there were a total of 804 suspected diphtheria cases, including 15 deaths, reported among the displaced Rohingya population in Cox's Bazar, with date of illness onset for almost all cases from 10 Nov 2017 through 12 Dec 2017. The news report above says that there are an additional 1571 suspected cases of this disease since 10 Nov 2017, for a total of 2373 cases, in the refugee camps at Cox's Bazar. Now 21 have died of diphtheria in the camps.

Rohingya refugees from Myanmar arrived in Cox's Bazar district of Chittagong division in Bangladesh, joining an existing refugee population, some of whom have been in the camps for years, others displaced more recently; as of late September 2017, Bangladesh was said to be sheltering 800 000 displaced Rohingya (https://www.unicefusa.org/stories/unicef-ramps-relief-myanmar-refugees/32834).

Maps of the region, showing Myanmar and Bangladesh, with the location of Cox's Bazar, can be found at https://goo.gl/maps/kpsb2JqD8sM2,
https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5516537,33788, and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5516537,148. - Mod.ML]
